https://click.convertkit-mail.com/v8uownqnkvcrhqq0pgsg/z2hghnhowwqgv7sp/aHR=
0cHM6Ly9sZWFybnV4LmRlc2lnbg=3D=3D
) will open Jan 12 for new enrollments =F0=9F=8E=89]

I randomly emailed my favorite salsa company (Mrs. Renfro=E2=80=99s) and
asked if I could tour the factory when I was in Texas last month.

To my surprise, they said: sure, what time?

I also brought my 9-month old, who posed for her first ad
campaign pitch.
I showed up with a list of questions about salsa: how do you come
up with new salsas? How do you test recipes? Have you had any big
flops?

But it turns out: they hardly think about recipes at all.

(It=E2=80=99s a multi-generation family business. All the best-sellers
were created 40 years ago. They haven=E2=80=99t launched a new product in
years.)

Instead, the day-to-day for them is all about forming long-term
relationships with high-quality vendors.

I found that amazing.

To make good salsa, don=E2=80=99t think about salsa =E2=80=93 think about f=
orming
long-term relationships with the best farms.

And, just the other day, I saw a parallel with UI design.

I was helping one of my students with redesigning a dev ops tool.
In particular, he was having a tough time styling the card title
(=E2=80=9Ctest=E2=80=9D) to look like a title.

=E2=80=8B
There are a couple fairly basic things you could do here to make
=E2=80=9Ctest=E2=80=9D look more like a title:

* Remove the blue coloring (so it doesn=E2=80=99t feel like a link)
* Make it bigger

But the results will ASTOUND you. Ready? KEEP SCROLLING.

You scrolled!
Ummmm, it=E2=80=99s fine. But it=E2=80=99s not good yet. It doesn=E2=80=99t=
 feel
designed.

So let=E2=80=99s switch gears. Instead of styling the title directly,
what if we styled elements around the title?

For instance:

* Added a bit more white space below the title to separate it
from the card content
* Add horizontal striping for the table rows, to make the table
feel more like one big element (weird UI fact: horizontal lines
in UI design always say =E2=80=9Cthe stuff under me goes together=E2=80=9D)
* Make the app background light gray, which will further
emphasize the (white) card, thereby indirectly making the title
seem more like a card title =F0=9F=A4=AF

=E2=80=8B
You know what? =E2=80=93 it=E2=80=99s much better!

We see this in a lot of places. If you=E2=80=99re having trouble styling
an element, focus instead on the elements around it.

Perhaps the most common scenario for this design judo is selected
states.

=E2=80=8B
If your active item is too light, don=E2=80=99t just make it darker =E2=80=
=93
also make the non-active items lighter!

And just as styling elements is about styling the elements around
them, remember: salsa is about relationships =E2=99=A5=EF=B8=8F.

